3.6. 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF89EF4AFF4EFAB9FDD0FA9E" authority="Burmeister, 1838" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[203,613,1292,1318]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phaneropterini">Phaneropterini Burmeister, 1838</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF89EF4AFF12FAE1FC7EFA63" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="description">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF89EF4AFF12FAE1FC7EFA63" blockId="33.[151,1437,1364,1499]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
This is a cosmopolite tribe, with 376 species, distributed in 29 genera, currently described (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF89EF4AFB2DFAE1FA24FAD6" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." box="[1192,1425,1364,1390]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" refId="ref30789" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org (accessed 13 March 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF89EF4AFA97FAE0FAF9FAD6" box="[1298,1356,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
). Three subtribes are found in the Neotropical Region: 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FF89EF4AFD76FACDFC1AFA2A" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1878" box="[755,943,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Anaulacomerina">Anaulacomerina</taxonomicName>
, Pelecynotina and Viadanina. The tribe was already recorded for the 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF89EF4AFE2AFA29FD8BFA0E" box="[431,574,1436,1462]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Paraná State</collectingRegion>
, when a species from the Iguaçu National Park was described (
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF89EF4AFA88FA29FF54FA62" author="Fianco, M. &amp; Cadena-Castaneda, O. J. &amp; Szinwelski, N. &amp; Faria, L. R. R." pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="365 - 376" refId="ref32343" refString="Fianco, M., Cadena-Castaneda, O. J., Szinwelski, N. &amp; Faria, L. R. R. (2019 a) A new Anaulacomera species (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae: Phaneropterinae) from the Iguacu National Park, southern Brazil. Zootaxa, 4700 (3), 365 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4700.3.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Fianco 
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF89EF4AFAE6FA28FA28FA0E" box="[1379,1437,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">et al.</emphasis>
2019a
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we present records for 16 species, belonging to five genera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
